A truck, loaded with 33,000 litres of petroleum product,  fell on Wednesday morning, at Barracks Bus Stop, along the Mile 2/Badagry Expressway, Lagos, spilling its content on the ground. A yet to be ascertained number of persons, according to unconfirmed report, died in the incident while scores of vehicles got burnt. The incident occurred at a bad spot in front of Onireke Police Station, Barracks bus stop. Details later… Fire razes 10 vehicles on Badagry expressway Many escape death as petrol tanker overturns 21 vehicles, 5 motorcycles burnt in Lagos tanker explosion